Spicy Cream Cold Foam.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou May Also Like: \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/starbucks-lavender-drinks-review/\"\u003eOur Honest Review of Starbucks New Lavender Drinks\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eWhat are the Starbucks Spicy Lemonade Refreshers?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSpicy is so hot right now. And by that, we mean it\u0026rsquo;s trending. According to Starbucks and Google search data, the term \u003cem\u003eswicy (\u003c/em\u003ewhich is a portmanteau for sweet and spicy) has seen many search spikes over the past five years. From\u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.ca/Mikes-Hot-Honey-12-oz/dp/B011LWRBES?crid=1LXKMKL2TFJMF\u0026amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.KRftnWxcvaNn-trhfS_s1GCJA2FSHjxoNf78rb2P29xQC4L1XnjvwGk5GHu8sfqzcuYf-bonDi_fdcSSQsyct486hmO8SKcNxCUFXqwkDeed-YAqNFLgMFP9yjbIaZJRkCPGo5VwdgQTFucW8EnTiVBgSimVvFWztTksXPMuWvd1s_nLtE1_qeW_7mbw6PwpdzpiD7uXRWbutkVgz-L-F6dXiE1oqWxZJmi-zF3gBQuTcAJTgs5-GgDop9k516eNyr1C1EkIRPGFTyLyxRPm6xBVta09-7Hb17QV1WkgkqE.SUFPYVseTsnC8RV1iCfUrs6uoylCrQ0czAkohV4HyrY\u0026amp;dib_tag=se\u0026amp;keywords=hot%2Bhoney\u0026amp;qid=1713299674\u0026amp;sprefix=hot%2Bhoney%2Caps%2C96\u0026amp;sr=8-2\u0026amp;th=1\u0026amp;linkCode=ll1\u0026amp;tag=foodnetworkca-20\u0026amp;linkId=23aad38425edc24e712de7f3f9779510\u0026amp;language=en_CA\u0026amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e hot honey\u003c/a\u003e to \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/spicy-watermelon-margarita/\"\u003espicy margaritas\u003c/a\u003e, Gen Z and Millenials can\u0026rsquo;t get enough of the sweet and spicy combo. Starbucks saw this and decided to fuel the fire by turning up the heat on their popular lemonade refreshers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Spicy Lemonade Refreshers are available in three flavours \u0026mdash; Spicy Strawberry, Spicy Dragonfruit and Spicy Pineapple. Each drink features the sweet flavours of fruit, real chunks of fruit, zesty lemonade and Starbucks\u0026rsquo; new Chili Powder blend to add a kick. Here is our ranking of the new drinks from our least favourite to favourite.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRelated: \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/starbucks-frozen-lemonades-ranked/\"\u003eWe Rank the New Starbucks Frozen Lemonades From Best to Worst\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"attachment_151331\" style=\"width: 858px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-151331\" class=\"size-large wp-image-151331\" src=\"https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-pineapple-refresher.jpg?w=848\" alt=\"\" width=\"848\" height=\"565\" srcset=\"https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-pineapple-refresher.jpg 848w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-pineapple-refresher.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-pineapple-refresher.jpg?resize=768,512 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\"\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-151331\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"\u003eStarbucks Canada\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eSpicy Pineapple Lemonade Refresher\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePineapple and \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/passionfruit-coconut-linzer-cookies-recipe/\"\u003epassionfruit flavours\u003c/a\u003e are shaken with ice, \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/pineapple-dream-dessert/\"\u003epineapple\u003c/a\u003e pieces, \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/ina-gartens-pink-lemonade/\"\u003elemonade\u003c/a\u003e and Starbucks Spicy Chili Powder Blend to create this bevy. In general, we are not the biggest fans of pineapple-flavoured drinks so it didn\u0026rsquo;t shock us that this was our least favourite new Starbucks menu item. We were getting more of a spicy and sour mix rather than sweet, so it was not a flavour combo we would typically go for. However, we did find this the least spicy of the three new offerings, so if you feel like you can\u0026rsquo;t take the heat, the Spicy Pineapple Lemonade Refresher might be for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"attachment_151332\" style=\"width: 858px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-151332\" class=\"size-large wp-image-151332\" src=\"https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-strawberry-refresher.jpg?w=848\" alt=\"\" width=\"848\" height=\"565\" srcset=\"https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-strawberry-refresher.jpg 848w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-strawberry-refresher.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-strawberry-refresher.jpg?resize=768,512 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\"\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-151332\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"\u003eStarbucks Canada\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eSpicy Strawberry Lemonade Refresher\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Spicy Strawberry Lemonade Refresher consists of strawberry and acai shaken with ice, \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/chinese-candied-strawberries-tanghulu/\"\u003estrawberry\u003c/a\u003e pieces, lemonade and Starbucks Spicy Chili Powder Blend. This one was sweet, thanks to the strawberry, while the lemonade offered zesty tartness to offset the sweet and spicy. This drink turned up the heat a bit more than the Spicy Pineapple Lemonade Refresher and we actually thought it was the perfect amount of spice. Although this one was not our number one favourite, in terms of flavour, we do think this is the one we\u0026rsquo;d most likely order again. It was mildly spicy and had the perfect blend of spicy, sweet, tart and zesty.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou May Also Like: \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/our-honest-review-chatime-new-sakura-bloom-spring-drinks/\"\u003eOur Honest Review of Chatime\u0026rsquo;s New Sakura Bloom Spring Drinks\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"attachment_151330\" style=\"width: 858px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-151330\" class=\"size-large wp-image-151330\" src=\"https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-dragonfruit-refresher.jpg?w=848\" alt=\"\" width=\"848\" height=\"565\" srcset=\"https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-dragonfruit-refresher.jpg 848w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-dragonfruit-refresher.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/spicy-dragonfruit-refresher.jpg?resize=768,512 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\"\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-151330\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"\u003eStarbucks Canada\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eSpicy Dragonfruit Lemonade Refresher\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith mango and dragonfruit flavours shaken with ice, dragonfruit pieces, lemonade and Starbucks Spicy Chili Powder Blend, the Spicy Dragonfruit Lemonade Refresher comes out on top for us. This was definitely the spiciest of the three and had our eyes watering. We also loved the combination of the \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/best-mango-recipes/\"\u003etropical mango\u003c/a\u003e and dragonfruit with those spicy notes from the spice blend. We felt like we were on a tropical vacation! If you want to add a different kind of kick, we think this drink would be incredible with a shot of \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/lemon-and-cucumber-gin-fizz/\"\u003egin\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/this-refreshing-brazilian-lemonade-margarita-is-the-drink-of-summer/\"\u003etequila\u003c/a\u003e. Now that is spicing it up!\u003c/p\u003e\n